---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="Learn about Forensic Darkness and our mission to inform and support crime victims.">
  <section class="py-12">
    <div class="container max-w-4xl">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-display font-bold mb-6">About Forensic Darkness</h1>

      <div class="prose-dark">
        <p class="lead text-xl text-fd-muted mb-8">
          Forensic Darkness is dedicated to informing victims with help and resources while exploring the psychology of serial killers and violent crime.
        </p>

        <h2>Our Mission</h2>
        <p>
          Serial killers don't just hatch overnightâ€”they are the product of years of circumstances and thought processes which makes killing the one thing that drives them forward. This site provides information about the many mental illnesses and personality disorders common among these offenders, as well as provide help for victims and families to help keep them safe from kidnappers, child molesters, and serial killers.
        </p>

        <p>
          We as a community need to know our enemy in order to educate our children on how to stay safe. This subject may not be the easiest to digest but it has been one of much interest.
        </p>

        <h2>What is Forensic Darkness?</h2>
        <p>
          Forensic darkness is the trauma caused to the victim. It represents the shadow that violent crime casts over survivors and their families. Through education and awareness, we aim to bring light to these dark corners of human experience.
        </p>

        <h2>Our Approach</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Education:</strong> Understanding criminal psychology to better protect ourselves and our communities</li>
          <li><strong>Awareness:</strong> Highlighting warning signs and prevention strategies</li>
          <li><strong>Support:</strong> Connecting victims with resources and assistance</li>
          <li><strong>Analysis:</strong> Case studies and forensic examination of crimes</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="bg-fd-card p-6 rounded-lg mt-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-display font-bold mb-4">Don't Be Scared, Be Aware!</h3>
          <p class="text-fd-muted mb-0">
            Safety comes first. Instead of being scared, be aware! A serial killer may not be who you imagine them to be, which means we all need to keep our eyes open. As humans we are instinctive. Trust your instincts and stay aware of the danger.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="mt-12">Our Contributors</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mt-6">
          <div class="bg-fd-card p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-lg mb-2">Jenny Montoya</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-fd-primary mb-3">M.A. Forensic Psychology</p>
            <p class="text-fd-muted text-sm">
              Jenny brings professional expertise in forensic psychology to her analysis of criminal behavior and victim support resources. Her articles focus on understanding the psychological factors behind violent crime and practical safety awareness.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-fd-card p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-lg mb-2">Victor J. Fisher</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-fd-primary mb-3">Forensic Science Writer</p>
            <p class="text-fd-muted text-sm">
              Victor contributes detailed case studies and forensic analysis, drawing lessons from historical crimes to inform modern awareness. His writing connects investigative procedures with practical insights for readers.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="mt-12">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Have questions or want to contribute? Reach out via our <a href="/contact" class="text-fd-primary hover:underline">contact page</a> or follow us on <a href="https://www.facebook.com/forensicdarknessserialkillings" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-fd-primary hover:underline">Facebook</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
